        <div class="grid-main__gutter-l">
            <h2 class="section-title">Intro</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-main__content grid-main__content--narrow">
            <p class="dropcap">At Abenity we send a *LOT* of email. Due to requirements we have around certain proprietary business rules, we had to roll our own system for managing lists and campaigns. One team member even had to devote about 80% of his time to creating and editing HTML email templates. We wanted to free up his time and empower our marketing team to do this work without needing help from the development team, and we wanted to refactor a legacy system that grew organically over time into something that was easily understood. I enjoy projects like this because I like helping the other teams at our company and because I like working closely with the backend to figure out the best way to build complex features like this.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <div class="grid-main u-margin--b-m">
            <div class="grid-main__gutter-l">
                <h2 class="section-title">Goals</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="grid-main__content grid-main__content--narrow">
                <p>There were two main problems that needed solving with this update. Number one, we needed to create an admin for managing campaigns and understanding how it coordinated with the mailing provider we were using to actually send the final email. This needed a whole new language developed around it so that new hires could intuitively understand the system as well as someone who had worked with it for years. Number two, we needed a way for someone with no HTML experience to be able to create custom HTML emails. Along with this goal, we also needed to create a system to quickly generate the forms needed to enter the content to create these emails.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-main u-margin--b-m">
            <div class="grid-main__gutter-l"></div>
            <div class="grid-main__content">
                <h3 class="hd-3">Template Development</h3>
                <div class="columns">
                    <p>There were main pieces to build for this project, enabling our marketing team to create and update HTML email templates, and managing the campaigns for the email sends, which including syncing with a third party service to send the emails. This would become a new section in a single page application built in VueJS that we use to maintain content internally.</p>

                    <p>First, I created a responsive HTML email that would work across  our testing suite (thanks Litmus!) without using media queries (thanks Gmail on Android!). Yes, it’s as gross and weird as it sounds. For making this base HTML email into configurable template variations, each mailing template has a set of JSON, that is fetched and transformed into a form by a Vue Component. Then there is a corresponding Blade template that reads the data created by the form and generates an HTML page. This is pulled into an iframe that is positioned by the form for an updated real time preview any time you save you work.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-main u-margin--b-m">
            <div class="grid-main__gutter-l"></div>
            <div class="grid-main__content grid-img">
                <figure class="grid__img grid__img--left">
                    <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/568x409.png?
                    text=Placeholder">
                    <figcaption class="grid-img__caption"><strong>Figure One:</strong> This is a very important screen that captures important details you need to see that will definitely make you hire me.</figcaption>
